I have projects using TensorFlow 1.14, so I would like to use the 1.14 docs for reference. Will the 1.14 docs be back up?

comments.comment: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/artemmavrin>@artemmavrin</denchmark-link> Where did you find those links on Tensorflow website? Thanks!

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/jvishnuvardhan>@jvishnuvardhan</denchmark-link> The links are similar to links I've been using as recently as earlier this week to access TensorFlow 1.14 documentation. The last such working link in by browser history is <denchmark-link:https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r1.14/api_docs/python/>https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r1.14/api_docs/python/</denchmark-link> from January 9, which currently redirects to <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/tree/r1.14/site/en/api_docs/python>https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/tree/r1.14/site/en/api_docs/python</denchmark-link> . I've been using the 1.15 documentation and 1.14 source code for reference in the meantime, but it would be very convenient for my projects that use 1.14 if I had the 1.14 documentation at my disposal. Thanks!

HI <denchmark-link:https://github.com/artemmavrin>@artemmavrin</denchmark-link> , this is works-as-intended. tensorflow.org is focused on TF2 now, but we'll continue to host the latest 1.x version on the site (1.15). We're archiving older versions in the tensorflow/docs GitHub repo under the version branch: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/tree/r1.14/site/en>https://github.com/tensorflow/docs/tree/r1.14/site/en</denchmark-link>
These docs can be navigated and previewed using the GitHub previewer.
